<TITLE> Two policemen remanded for mugging </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (bdnews24.com)The two police sub-inspectors arrested on charges of snatching 86,000 riyals from a Bangladeshi expatriate living in Saudi Arabia was remanded for five days Monday. The Detective Branch of Dhaka Metropolitan Police took the two to court and sought permission for five days to interrogate them. Additional chief metropolitan magistrate Golam Rabbani granted the remand prayer. The two arrested SIs are Amir Hossain of Pallabi Police Station and Selim Mollah of Paltan Police Station. Tejgaon police SI Matiar Rahman told bdnews24.com that a case had been filed in connection with the incident. "A mobile phone had been seized from one of them. Attempts are underway to recover the snatched money," he said. In the case filed Friday, a day after the incident, Mohammad Ripon, who came back from Saudi Arabia, alleged that the two policemen had bundled him into a highway patrol car near Mohakhali bus terminal, bound his hands and blindfolded him before robbing. bdnew
